reviews.text: It is located in a small street with many restaurants. Lunch set has 4 choices in western style, including soup, main course and coffee / tea.  It seems run by a small family. Atmosphere is nice but a bit dark. Price is very reasonable and you will get a bit discount if you arrive after 13:30. Taste is ok and coffee is good.

The steak in the lunch set is really good with reasonable prices. Owning to the limited space in the restaurant, the environment may be a little bit stuffy. But still, really recommended to have a try!

Very delicious cuisine
The special decorations and comfortable environment!
Good service and delicious food
I love the slow-cooked Japanese chicken breast XO tomatoes sauce linguine and fried North American stripped bass with roasted vegetables and truffles cream mashed potatoes
Nice steak with reasonable price

If your menu states "roasted vegetables" you need to have at least 2 roasted vegetables for that to be accurate.
Mashed potato was packet mix, somewhat grainy and bland. On a previous visit, the  mash was at least real. Lamb was well cooked but as a meal it is overpriced.
